	"packageName": "await-to-done",
	"packageVersion": "1.2.0",
	"readme": [
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\">\n\n# await-to-done\n\n**Async await wrapper for easy error handling**\n\nZero dependencies • ES5 compatible • TypeScript ready\n\n[![npm version][npm-image]][npm-url]\n[![npm downloads][download-image]][download-url]\n[![gzip][gzip-image]][gzip-url]\n[![License][license-image]][license-url]\n\n[![Sonar][sonar-image]][sonar-url]\n\n</div>\n\n## Why?\n\nStop writing try-catch blocks everywhere. "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`await-to-done`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " wraps your promises and returns a tuple "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`[error, data]`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " for elegant error handling.\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\n// Before 😫\ntry {\n  const data = await fetchData()\n  // handle data\n} catch (error) {\n  // handle error\n}\n\n// After 😍\nimport to from 'await-to-done'\n\nconst [error, data] = await to(fetchData())\nif (error) {\n  // handle error\n}\n// handle data\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Install\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```bash\npnpm add await-to-done\n# or\nnpm install await-to-done\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Usage\n\n### Single Promise\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\nimport to from 'await-to-done'\n\nconst [error, user] = await to(fetchUser(id))\n\nif (error) {\n  console.error('Failed to fetch user:', error)\n  return\n}\n\nconsole.log('User:', user)\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n### Multiple Promises\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\nimport to from 'await-to-done'\n\n// Pass multiple promises as arguments\nconst [error, [user, posts]] = await to(fetchUser(id), fetchPosts(id))\n\n// Or pass an array\nconst [error, results] = await to([fetchUser(id), fetchPosts(id)])\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n### Custom Error Type\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\nimport to from 'await-to-done'\n\ninterface ApiError {\n  code: number\n  message: string\n}\n\nconst [error, data] = await to<string, ApiError>(fetchData())\nif (error) {\n  console.log(error.code, error.message)\n}\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n### Browser / CDN\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```html\n<script src=\"https://unpkg.com/await-to-done/dist/index.umd.js\"></script>\n<script>\n  const [error, data] = await awaitToDone(fetch('/api/data'))\n</script>\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## API\n\n### "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`to<T, E>(promise)`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n| Parameter   | Type                                   | Description             |\n| ----------- | -------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`promise`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "   | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Promise<T>`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "                           | A promise to wrap       |\n| **Returns** | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Promise<[E, undefined] \\| [null, T]>`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " | Tuple of error and data |\n\n### "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`to<P>(promises)`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n| Parameter   | Type                                       | Description                 |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------------ | --------------------------- |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`promises`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "  | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Promise[]`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "                                | Array of promises           |\n| **Returns** | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Promise<[Error, undefined] \\| [null, P]>`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " | Tuple with array of results |\n\n## Types\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\n// Result tuple type\ntype Result<T, E = Error> = [E, undefined] | [null, T]\n\n// Async result type\ntype AsyncResult<T, E = Error> = Promise<Result<T, E>>\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Bundle Size\n\n| File            | Size (min + gzip) |\n| --------------- | ----------------- |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`index.min.mjs`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " | ~300 B            |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`index.umd.js`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "  | ~400 B            |\n\n## Comparison\n\n| Feature           | await-to-done | await-to-js |\n| ----------------- | ------------- | ----------- |\n| Dependencies      | 0             | 0           |\n| TypeScript types  | ✅ Built-in   | ❌ Separate |\n| Multiple promises | ✅            | ❌          |\n| Array support     | ✅            | ❌          |\n| ES5 compatible    | ✅            | ✅          |\n| Size              | ~300 B        | ~200 B      |\n\n## License\n\n[MIT]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "LICENSE",
			"target": 2
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ")\n\n[npm-image]: https://img.shields.io/npm/v/await-to-done.svg\n[npm-url]: https://npmjs.org/package/await-to-done\n[download-image]: https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/await-to-done.svg\n[download-url]: https://npmjs.org/package/await-to-done\n[gzip-image]: http://img.badgesize.io/https://unpkg.com/await-to-done/dist/index.global.prod.js?compression=gzip&label=gzip%20size:%20JS\n[gzip-url]: http://img.badgesize.io/https://unpkg.com/await-to-done/dist/index.global.prod.js?compression=gzip&label=gzip%20size:%20JS\n[license-image]: https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-blue.svg\n[license-url]: "
		},
		{
